description:
Ready in 4-5 minutes. An Italian dinner just isn't complete without New York Brand Texas Toast, America's favorite Garlic Bread! Ready in just 4-5 minutes - it's the easiest way to please your family at dinner. Our Beginnings: Over 50 years ago, the Penn family moved their small family bakery from New York to Cleveland and continued to specialize in the crusty, chewy-textured, hearth-baked breads that are still popular in Europe today. Over time, the Penn family created the New York Brand line of Texas Toasts, Garlic Knots, Breadsticks, Garlic Loaves, and Ciabatta Rolls that have become favorites across the US. 100% recycled paperboard.

Directions:

Baking: Conventional Oven (For Crisper Crust After baking, place slices under broiler for 1-2 minutes): Preheat oven to 425 degrees F. Remove bread from bag and separate slices. Place slices flat on baking sheet/aluminum foil. Bake 5-7 minutes on middle shelf of oven. To brown on both sides, turn slices over after 3 minutes. Toaster Oven (For Crisper Crust After baking, place slices under broiler for 1-2 minutes): Preheat oven to 425 degrees F. Remove bread from bag and separate slices. Place slices flat on baking sheet/aluminum foil. Bake 4-5 minutes on middle shelf of oven. To brown on both sides, turn slices over after 2 minutes. Stove Top: Remove bread from bag and separate slices. Place slices in non-stick pan and cover. Heat at medium setting for 1-1/2 to 3 minutes on each side. On the Grill: Remove bread from bag and separate slices. Grill over medium coals for 1-1/2 to 3 minutes. Turn toast several times (15-30 second intervals). Serve warm. Keep frozen.

Heat 20-25 minutes (Ovens vary - heating times are approximate, and may need adjustment. If thawed, reduce heating times). Carefully remove foil and turn out of pan onto a serving dish (For variety, sprinkle with chopped nuts, slivered almonds, dried cranberries or raisins). Best used within 30 days after purchase. Keep frozen until ready to heat & serve.

description:

Directions:
Pan: Place desired number of rolls on a lightly greased cookie sheet or in a cake pan 1-3 inches apart. Brush tops of rolls with melted butter or margarine, or spray with cooking spray. Thaw: Let dough thaw in a warm place (up to 110 degrees) free of drafts (1-2 hours), or covered in refrigerator overnight. Rise: Let dough rise until double in size (2-3 hours). Bake: Bake in a pre-heated 375 degrees oven 10-14 minutes. Remove from oven. Lightly brush with additional melted butter or margarine. Turn rolls out of pan immediately to cool. (Alternate Quick-Thaw & Rise Method): Heat oven to lowest setting for 5 minutes, then turn oven off. Place panned, basted rolls in oven to thaw and rise (1-2 hours).
